CS_DEF_EEPROM_TABLE_FILENAME.title: EEPROM File Table -- default table filename
CS_DEF_EEPROM_TABLE_FILENAME.description: This parameter defines the default filename for the EEPROM addresses File Table.
CS_DEF_EEPROM_TABLE_FILENAME.limits: The string length (including string terminator) cannot exceed #OS_MAX_PATH_LEN.  (limit is not verified)

CS_DEF_MEMORY_TABLE_FILENAME.title: Memory Address File Table -- default table filename
CS_DEF_MEMORY_TABLE_FILENAME.description: This parameter defines the default filename for the Memory addresses File Table.
CS_DEF_MEMORY_TABLE_FILENAME.limits: The string length (including string terminator) cannot exceed #OS_MAX_PATH_LEN.  (limit is not verified)

CS_DEF_TABLES_TABLE_FILENAME.title: Tables File Table -- default table filename
CS_DEF_TABLES_TABLE_FILENAME.description: This parameter defines the default filename for the Tables List File Table.
CS_DEF_TABLES_TABLE_FILENAME.limits: The string length (including string terminator) cannot exceed #OS_MAX_PATH_LEN.  (limit is not verified)

CS_PIPE_DEPTH.title: Application Pipe Depth
CS_PIPE_DEPTH.description: This parameter defines the depth of the CS input pipe.  The depth should be deep enough to accommodate all of the DS command packets and all of the subscribed telemetry packets that might be generated by applications with a priority higher than the CS application.
CS_PIPE_DEPTH.limits: The value must be greater than zero and cannot exceed the definition of #CFE_SB_MAX_PIPE_DEPTH.

CS_MAX_NUM_EEPROM_TABLE_ENTRIES.title: Maximum number of entries in the Eeprom table to checksum
CS_MAX_NUM_EEPROM_TABLE_ENTRIES.description: Maximum number of entries that can be in the table of Eeprom areas to checksum.
CS_MAX_NUM_EEPROM_TABLE_ENTRIES.limits: This parameter is limited by the uint16 datatype that defines it. This parameter is limited to 65535.

CS_MAX_NUM_MEMORY_TABLE_ENTRIES.title: Maximum number of entries in the Memory table to checksum
CS_MAX_NUM_MEMORY_TABLE_ENTRIES.description: Maximum number of entries that can be in the table of Memory areas to checksum.
CS_MAX_NUM_MEMORY_TABLE_ENTRIES.limits: This parameter is limited by the uint16 datatype that defines it. This parameter is limited to 65535.

CS_MAX_NUM_TABLES_TABLE_ENTRIES.title: Maximum number of tables to checksum
CS_MAX_NUM_TABLES_TABLE_ENTRIES.description: Maximum number of entries in the table of tables to checksum
CS_MAX_NUM_TABLES_TABLE_ENTRIES.limits: This parameter is limited by the maximum number of tables allowed in the system. This parameter is limited to #CFE_TBL_MAX_NUM_TABLES

CS_MAX_NUM_APP_TABLE_ENTRIES.title: Maximum number of applications to checksum
CS_MAX_NUM_APP_TABLE_ENTRIES.description: Maximum number of entries in the table of applications to checksum.
CS_MAX_NUM_APP_TABLE_ENTRIES.limits: This parameter is limited by the maximum number of applications allowed in the system. This parameter is limited to #CFE_ES_MAX_APPLICATIONS

CS_DEFAULT_BYTES_PER_CYCLE.title: Default number of bytes to checksum per cycle
CS_DEFAULT_BYTES_PER_CYCLE.description: The default number of bytes that are checksummed in a single CS cycle.
CS_DEFAULT_BYTES_PER_CYCLE.limits: This parameter is limited by the maximum value allowed by the data type. In this case, the data type is an unsigned 32-bit integer, so the valid range is 0 to 0xFFFFFFFF.  Note that '0' is a valid value, and will result in a checksum of 0.

CS_CHILD_TASK_PRIORITY.title: CS Child Task Priority
CS_CHILD_TASK_PRIORITY.description: Priority of child tasks created by CS.  Lower numbers are higher priority, with 1 being the highest priority in the case of a child task.
CS_CHILD_TASK_PRIORITY.limits: Valid range for a child task is 1 to 255, but the priority cannot be higher (lower number) than the CS App priority.

CS_CHILD_TASK_DELAY.title: Delay between checksumming cycles for child task
CS_CHILD_TASK_DELAY.description: CS child tasks perform checksum cycles like the main App. Since the child tasks aren't scheduled, there needs to be some other mechanism to prevent it from hogging the CPU. This parameter specifies the number of milliseconds to delay in between cycles.
CS_CHILD_TASK_DELAY.limits: CS does not place limits on this parameter. It is intended to be configurable to prevent the child task from hogging the CPU.

CS_STARTUP_TIMEOUT.title: Timeout for waiting for other apps to start
CS_STARTUP_TIMEOUT.description: CS waits for all of the other applications that are listed in the startup script to start before entering its main loop. If not all of those apps start, CS can pend indefinitely without a timeout. Once CS waits this amount of time ( in milliseconds) it will start regardless of the status of the rest of the apps in the startup script.
CS_STARTUP_TIMEOUT.limits: CS does not place limits on this parameter. It is intended to be configurable to allow enough time for all apps to start.

CS_OSCS_CHECKSUM_STATE.title: Desired state of the checksumming of OS code segment at power on
CS_OSCS_CHECKSUM_STATE.description: This determines the default state the checksumming of OS code segment should be in at power on.
CS_OSCS_CHECKSUM_STATE.limits: This can either be CS_STATE_ENABLED or CS_STATE_DISABLED

CS_CFECORE_CHECKSUM_STATE.title: Desired state of the checksumming of CFE core checksum at power on
CS_CFECORE_CHECKSUM_STATE.description: This determines the default state the checksumming of CFE core should be in at power on.
CS_CFECORE_CHECKSUM_STATE.limits: This can either be CS_STATE_ENABLED or CS_STATE_DISABLED.

CS_EEPROM_TBL_POWERON_STATE.title: Desired state of the EEPROM table at power on
CS_EEPROM_TBL_POWERON_STATE.description: This determines the default state the EEPROM table should be in at power on.
CS_EEPROM_TBL_POWERON_STATE.limits: This can either be CS_STATE_ENABLED or CS_STATE_DISABLED

CS_MEMORY_TBL_POWERON_STATE.title: Desired state of the EEPROM table at power on
CS_MEMORY_TBL_POWERON_STATE.description: This determines the default state the Memory table should be in at power on
CS_MEMORY_TBL_POWERON_STATE.limits: This can either be CS_STATE_ENABLED or CS_STATE_DISABLED

CS_APPS_TBL_POWERON_STATE.title: Desired state of the Applications table at power on
CS_APPS_TBL_POWERON_STATE.description: This determines the default state the EEPROM table should be in at power on.
CS_APPS_TBL_POWERON_STATE.limits: This can either be CS_STATE_ENABLED or CS_STATE_DISABLED.

CS_TABLES_TBL_POWERON_STATE.title: Desired state of the Tables table at power on
CS_TABLES_TBL_POWERON_STATE.description: This determines the default state the EEPROM table should be in at power on.
CS_TABLES_TBL_POWERON_STATE.limits: This can either be CS_STATE_ENABLED or CS_STATE_DISABLED

CS_PRESERVE_STATES_ON_PROCESSOR_RESET.title: Whether to preserve checksum states on processor reset
CS_PRESERVE_STATES_ON_PROCESSOR_RESET.description: This determines whether to preserve checksum enabled/disabled states on processor reset

CS_CDS_NAME.title: Name of the Critical Data Store Used for CS
CS_CDS_NAME.description: Name of the Critical Data Store for CS. This CDS is used to preserve the checksum enabled states for EERPOM, Memory, Apps, Tables tables as well as OS code segment and cFE core states
CS_CDS_NAME.limits: Must be a unique string with regards to CDS

CS_MISSION_REV.title: Mission specific version number for CS application
CS_MISSION_REV.description: An application version number consists of four parts: major version number, minor version number, revision number and mission specific revision number. The mission specific revision number is defined here and the other parts are defined in 'cs_version.h'.
CS_MISSION_REV.limits: Must be defined as a numeric value that is greater than or equal to zero.
